commit.message:
Rectify documentation about Docker storage driver

Commit 9085de75469a added a note to the README document saying that
ebuildtester required the Device Mapper storage driver [0] in Docker.
This is not generally true.

Each Docker storage driver comes with a set of options [1] it supports.
One storage driver option (`size=50G`) which had been hardcoded in
ebuildtester had been reason for that requirement.

Later, commit cf1fe379ff49, among other things, removed the hardcoded
option and allowed users to specify storage options. The README document
had, however, not been modified accordingly.

This commit makes up for that by changing the section in question in the
README file. This should especially help first-time users of
ebuildtester to get it up and running.

[0] https://docs.docker.com/storage/storagedriver/device-mapper-driver/
[1] https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/commandline/dockerd/
      #options-per-storage-driver
